node.text:
OUR OFFICIAL TRAILER!! This is so crazy it’s finally here!! We had so much fun making this film and can’t wait for you to see it!! Watch it tonight!!! 

Check us out on Video On Demand/Digital Everywhere and in select theaters!!! 🙌🏽💀👊🏽

Thank you for all your support!!

node.text:
like all the self tapes at home and no shaving all November. One thing that’s consistent, @kingcgillette helps me prepare for any role or even anything life throws at me. Even if it’s a cowboy trying to sell timeshares. Stay Ready and you don’t have to get ready. 

#kingcgillettepartner #kcg #onefitkit

node.text: #stayhome I haven’t been able to train like I normally do, eat how I normally eat and I realized I still have full control over what I choose to do with my time. So with all that’s going on I’m challenging myself to do as many pushups as I can until I can hit 100 pushups without stopping. This is day 1! No Excuses. Just Focus and dedication. 👊🏽 Challenge yourself to do something you’ve never done before. And everybody please stay safe and healthy ❤️ were going to get through this but we’ve got to make the right choices.. together! 🙏🏽

I wanted to partner with the LAFD foundation in giving away a brand new Indian motorcycle to help raise money for the LAFD. Tickets are $25 to enter and every $100 you spend you get an extra ticket, which makes 5 entries! It’s that simple and it’s for a great cause! The link is in my bio!! Don’t wait! Enter to win and Donate today! 🔥❤️ Thank you guys!! Link is in my bio to donate

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Brock O'Hurn in Los Angeles, California with @brockohurnpodcast. May be an image of 1 person and beard.

node.text:
Just popping in to hi! 👋🏽

I’ve got this incredible post workout endorphin and dopamine rush! Feeling absolutely amazing. Spent the whole weekend traveling to Atlanta working on my physical health and can’t wait to share what I did there with you guys. 

All I can say is I’m grateful to be alive and do what I love on a daily basis especially knowing that wasn’t always the case. Constantly working towards improving myself  and my life experience anywhere I can. 

If you want something, be it your success in any field. Find the core root of what is preventing that success and rebuild from the ground up.

Also, my podcast is coming soon and I can’t wait to share with you some of the conversations and people I’ve already had with guests as well. Going deeper than I ever could on just an Instagram post.

Just out here trying to spread good vibes 😏🙌🏽 wish me luck lol

Have a great day everyone!! Stay Positive and Never Settle for less a than you deserve 

Also… this is my last day in my 20’s. What a wild ride it’s been 😎 
30’s.. Time to WORK!!!

node.text:
I want to start off by saying this is a selfish post. I’m posting this purely for myself so I can look back at this years from today and feel as much gratitude then as I do now for this woman. And second that there hasn’t been a time she hasn’t hidden from a photo from as long as I can remember. This woman is beyond beautiful. I only wish she could see herself through my eyes. Then she would know how beautiful she truly is.

My mother. The woman who brought me in to this world. I love you more than anything. 

I cherish days like this because they are so rare, I feel. Simple and filled with love. 

Mother’s are the most powerful and important beings on this planet in my opinion. 

If you go to the last slide you’ll see something I gave my mom when I was 12 ☘️ from a trip I did to Ireland with a friend and his family. 

That’s 18 years ago and I have long forgotten about it until this day. When she pulled it out of her wallet and let me know shes carried it every day since… 

I am grateful beyond any words that are possible in any language, for your strength, your love and for you being my mother. I wouldn’t trade it for anything. 

I love you mom. Always.

node.text:
So this post has been incredibly hard for me to post. Slide 1 is me a few days ago. After 4 months of putting my head down and getting to work. Day in and day out. Slide 2 and 3 are me the day I decided to stop listening to doctors and chiropractors and my depression telling me not to workout because it’ll only make my injuries worse. Slide 4 was before it all.

During the beginning of covid I never realized how big of an anchor staying fit was in relation to my mental health. I knew it was big but not how big. Something I don’t talk about often and I think I should, is that I grew up with clinical depression. 

I used to be embarrassed of this to be honest. Now I’m grateful. But it’s the reason I always tell people to stay positive and know the best is yet to come. 

I always used health and fitness to claw my way out of the darkness. Until it was virtually taken away from me due to gyms closing and multiple injuries simultaneously. 

And it lead to one thing after another. Until I found myself succumbing to terrible habits. Eating terribly, sleeping terribly and lost all of my confidence. 

I somehow booked a show that required me to be in shape and I’ve been working on myself full steam ever sense. 

I did it before when I weighed 130lbs at 6’3” and everyone told me I’d never have muscle. That my genetics will always be skinny. 

Just like back then.. I took my life in to my own hands. I’ve studied countless hours. Not only on how to help my mental state but my physical. Introducing recovery, proper nutrition, eating to heal, stretching, meditations are some of the few habits I now do daily to sustain happiness.

I knew, I just needed to FOCUS & have DISCIPLINE. 

Many wouldn’t believe I ever got out of shape in the first place. I’ve always been that guy who’s been healthy and in shape. But the proof is in the pudding.. and the cake.. and the fast food and ice cream. Oh and let’s not forget the PIZZA. Lol 

I’m saying all this so that hopefully someone who needs to hear it takes action, To Heal, To grow, To research & to work towards being their best self. Happy. 

I have more to say but I think I’ll do a podcast. Instagram is saying it’s 2 long lol
God Bless

node.text:
Happy Birthday Brother!!!! @mortenofficial 

We quickly became friends and you were one of the first I met on my journey to LA almost 10 years ago. I’ve been on stage with you in front of thousands in places all over the world. I’ve seen your career take off and nothing makes me happier than seeing my brother win. Now you’re touring the world making music with the greats. You’ve had me try more weird food than I would have ever in this lifetime and workout more times when I’d rather have taken a nap. You’ve pushed me to be a better version of myself and I hope I’ve returned the favor. 

I don’t say it lightly. You are not just a friend. You are FAMILY. 👊🏽

I’m proud of you and I look forward to when we can celebrate this day together. In person! 

The Best is Yet to Come!!

Happy Mother’s Day to the strongest woman I know. I can’t believe it’s already been 30 years together. I am grateful for you beyond measure. 

I don’t know how you raised 5 kids on your own but I do know I love you and look forward to the next 30. 

I love you Mom. Happy Mother’s Day ❤️
